"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-07-14-year-old-olympian-reveals-unusual-gift-parents-winning-gold-21381143\", \"text\": \"Arisa Trew,Australia's youngest Olympic champion inParis, revealed the unusual gift her parents are gifting her after she claimed skateboarding gold.  The 14-year-old produced a superb display on four wheels to earn gold with a score of 93.18 asJapan's Cocona Hiraki andTeam GB's Sky Brown took silver and bronze respectively.  However, the medal is not the only thing that the teenager will be rewarded with after revealing that her parents promised to get her a rather unusual winning gift: a pet duck.  'My parents promised if I won the gold medal I would get a pet duck,' Trew told the Today show back in Australia.  Follow Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  'Because they are really cute, then I can take it on walks and take it to the skate park.  'My parents definitely would not let me get a dog or a cat because we are travelling so much right now.  'But I feel like a duck might be a little bit easier, and\\u2026 I do not know, I just want a duck.  'It will just be in my yard and I will get a little pool thing for it.'  Speaking more generally on her Olympic victory, she said: 'It was just crazy, and so exciting. I could not believe it when I knew that I was the winner of the Olympics. This being my first Olympics - it's just insane.  'It's super cool that I have won the gold medal - it's been a dream, I am so excited.  'It's a little bit heavier than I thought, but it's like - beautiful.'  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:Why do athletes ring the bell in the Stade de France at the Paris 2024 Olympics?  ArrowMORE:Team GB's Olympic star Jake Jarman hints he could be open to switching nations in the future  ArrowMORE:American athlete scores 0.0 after nightmare dive at Paris Olympics  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"